The nurse smiles. At least I think she does, “That was my next question.
Do you remember how you got here?”
The tears budded in my eyes spill over as I look around again for my
stepbrother, shaking my head, “Did something happen to me at the club?
Did someone-“
“No.” Andrew practically spits out, sounding breathless, “No kid, nothing
like that.”
My shaky breath is the only sound among the machines for a fat minute,
